http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/VS-sees-political-plot/article14015847.ece

Leader of the Opposition V.S. Achuthanandan has termed the CBI decision to arraign Communist Party of India (Marxist) Kannur district unit secretary P. Jayarajan as an accused in the Kathiroor Manoj murder case the outcome of a political conspiracy involving the RSS and the Congress. In a statement here on Friday, Mr. Achuthanandan said the CBI investigation itself was the result of a conspiracy involving BJP-RSS leadership, Chief Minister Oommen Chandy and Home Minister Ramesh Chennithala. The State government had left the investigation in the case to CBI after Union Home Minister Rajnath Singh made a declaration to that effect in Kannur. ‘‘Conspiracy’In a statement, the CPI(M) State secretariat came down heavily on the CBI decision to arraign Mr. Jayarajan as an accused in the case and termed it part of a conspiracy involving RSS and Congress.